reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 8, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I ordered these for a gift I’m putting together for a friend and needed small, compact tissues for one of the pages. The tissue packaging is not only adorable, but so thin that it could be placed in smaller areas out of sight. They don’t take up much room and can be used for anything. In terms of the actual tissue - the Kleenex is kinda rough, so if you’re using it for wiping/blowing your nose I’d advise against it only because it feels like sandpaper being swiped across your face. These are made more for heavy spills or even wedding “happy tears” tissues. It comes with a pack of 30, but it’s more like 60 because each pack has two sides of tissues. Overall, a solid 5/5 is given due to the small compact each thing holds.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute little packest
reviews.reviewText: I always have to have tissue on me. If not for my allergies then for use in my role as a Nana. My grandchildren expect it of me now lol. I went looking for different options when I could not find any little packs at my local W- M- store. These were cute at a better bargain. One little granddaughter always asks me for a pack to put in her coat pocket, she is going to love these.

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Convenient for easy storage and surprisingly soft.
reviews.reviewText: My allergies frequently act up so I decided to try these. First of all the packaging is super cute! Second despite being made of wood pulp these tissues are surprisingly soft. Each pack is folded so they can easily fit in your bag, desk, car or wherever you put them. Also there are 10 tissues in each pack, 5 on each side. My only complaint is that it isn’t as absorbent as Kleenex.
